<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk.BlazorWebAssembly">

  <PropertyGroup>
    <TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>
    <Nullable>enable</Nullable>
    <ImplicitUsings>enable</ImplicitUsings>
    <Version>0.6.0</Version>
    <AssemblyVersion>0.6.0.0</AssemblyVersion>
    <FileVersion>0.6.0.0</FileVersion>
    <Authors>LastOnionKnight</Authors>
    <Description>Tonberry Tactics — companion web app for the in-game plugin. AskMrRobot-style hybrid gear optimizer for FFXIV. Pure-Math by default, Balance preset queued, exports plans back to the plugin via GG-PLAN:v1: strings. v0.6.0 ("Gear Division") is the full design port from Claude Design's React prototype: TLF Gear Division masthead with circle-logo crest, onion-shield TLF stamp, Evercold expansion banner, FF dialog-box import section, three-column layout (Adventurer card / center stack / right rail), full gear grid with materia dots, stat profile with cap bars, Materia Advisor with circled-number rec rows, Meld Audit panel, 21-job picker, CSS-animated walking Tonberry footer sprite. Pairs with plugin v0.6.0+ in lockstep. Wire-format prefixes (GG-EXPORT:v1:, GG-PLAN:v1:) unchanged — versioned identifiers, not brand names.</Description>
    <RepositoryUrl>https://github.com/LastOnionKnight/TonberryTactics</RepositoryUrl>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.WebAssembly" Version="10.0.0" />
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.WebAssembly.DevServer" Version="10.0.0" PrivateAssets="all" />
  </ItemGroup>

</Project>
